<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-532-202  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 532 202.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>NetWare Technical Journal  July 1989 v1 n3 p62(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Using AFP for DOS clients. (AppleTalk Filing Protocol )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anderson, Milton.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>AppleTalk Filing Protocol (AFP) makes resources once exclusivelyMacintosh available to other operating systems now that it hasbeen integrated into NetWare for Macintosh.andP;  Macintoshworkstations can have access to network resources; DOS and OS/2workstations have access to resources that were once exclusivelyMacintosh.andP;  Support of AFP is possible with the expansion of theNetWare Core Protocol (NCP) and with changes to NetWare's filingsystem.andP;  Network volume access is allowed by the Macintoshoperating system through a translator, therefore programmingdirectly to AFP is not needed.andP;  A basic understanding of AFP andthe Macintosh file system is necessary before accessingMacintosh-specific files from a DOS client.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   NetWare for Macintosh (Educational software) (usage)AppleTalk (Local area network) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Network Operating SystemsProtocolProgrammingAccess MethodsNetwork Access ProceduresLocal Area Networks.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogramchart.andO;Caption:   Source code to a DOS program that uses AFP calls. (program)Assembly call levels. (program)Apple network environment. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>